gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Nets 129, Magic 101
gameRecap.excerpt: The Magic snap their 9 game win streak as they fall to the Nets, 129-101. Mikal Bridges led all scorers with 42 points (34 in the 1st Half), along with five rebounds and three assists for the Nets, while Spencer Dinwiddie added 22 points, four rebounds and three assists in the victory. Paolo Banchero tallied 19 points, 10 rebounds and eight assists for the Magic in the losing effort. The Nets improve to 10-9 on the season, while the Magic fall to 14-6.
